27/* see comment in gvariant-serialiser.c about this madness.
28 *
29 * we use this to get testing of non-strictly-aligned GVariant instances
30 * on machines that can tolerate it. it is necessary to support this
31 * because some systems have malloc() that returns non-8-aligned
32 * pointers. it is necessary to have special support in the tests
33 * because on most machines malloc() is 8-aligned.
34 */
35#define ALIGN_BITS(sizeof (struct { char a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble
z; } b; }) - 9) (sizeof (struct { char a; union { \
36 guint64 x; void *y; gdouble z; } b; }) - 9)

38static gboolean
39randomly (gdouble prob)
40{
41 return g_test_rand_double_range (0, 1) < prob;
42}

189static GVariantType *
190append_tuple_type_string (GString *string,
191 GString *description,
192 gboolean definite,
193 gint depth)
194{
195 GVariantType *result, *other_result;
196 GVariantType **types;
197 gint size;
198 gsize i;
199
200 g_string_append_c (string, '(')g_string_append_c_inline (string, '(');
201 g_string_append (description, "t of [");
202
203 size = g_test_rand_int_range (0, 20);
204 types = g_new (GVariantType *, size + 1)(GVariantType * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (size
+ 1); gsize __s = sizeof (GVariantType *); gpointer __p; if (
__s == 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
205
206 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
207 {
208 types[i] = append_type_string (string, description, definite, depth);
209
210 if (i < size - 1)
211 g_string_append (description, ", ");
212 }
213
214 types[i] = NULL((void*)0);
215
216 g_string_append_c (description, ']')g_string_append_c_inline (description, ']');
217 g_string_append_c (string, ')')g_string_append_c_inline (string, ')');
218
219 result = g_variant_type_new_tuple ((gpointer) types, size);
220 other_result = g_variant_type_new_tuple ((gpointer) types, -1);
221 g_assert_true (g_variant_type_equal (result, other_result))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_type_equal (result, other_result)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 221
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_type_equal (result, other_result)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
222 g_variant_type_free (other_result);
223 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
224 g_variant_type_free (types[i]);
225 g_free (types);
226
227 return result;
228}

230/* given a valid type string, make it invalid */
231static gchar *
232invalid_mutation (const gchar *type_string)
233{
234 gboolean have_parens, have_braces;
235
236 /* it's valid, so '(' implies ')' and same for '{' and '}' */
237 have_parens = strchr (type_string, '(') != NULL((void*)0);
238 have_braces = strchr (type_string, '{') != NULL((void*)0);
239
240 if (have_parens && have_braces && randomly (0.3))
241 {
242 /* swap a paren and a brace */
243 gchar *pp, *bp;
244 gint np, nb;
245 gchar p, b;
246 gchar *new;
247
248 new = g_strdup (type_string);
249
250 if (randomly (0.5))
251 p = '(', b = '{';
252 else
253 p = ')', b = '}';
254
255 np = nb = 0;
256 pp = bp = new - 1;
257
258 /* count number of parens/braces */
259 while ((pp = strchr (pp + 1, p))) np++;
260 while ((bp = strchr (bp + 1, b))) nb++;
261
262 /* randomly pick one of each */
263 np = g_test_rand_int_range (0, np) + 1;
264 nb = g_test_rand_int_range (0, nb) + 1;
265
266 /* find it */
267 pp = bp = new - 1;
268 while (np--) pp = strchr (pp + 1, p);
269 while (nb--) bp = strchr (bp + 1, b);
270
271 /* swap */
272 g_assert_true (*bp == b && *pp == p)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (*bp == b && *pp == p) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 272, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "*bp == b && *pp == p" "' should be TRUE"); }
while (0);
273 *bp = p;
274 *pp = b;
275
276 return new;
277 }
278
279 if ((have_parens || have_braces) && randomly (0.3))
280 {
281 /* drop a paren/brace */
282 gchar *new;
283 gchar *pp;
284 gint np;
285 gchar p;
286
287 if (have_parens)
288 if (randomly (0.5)) p = '('; else p = ')';
289 else
290 if (randomly (0.5)) p = '{'; else p = '}';
291
292 new = g_strdup (type_string);
293
294 np = 0;
295 pp = new - 1;
296 while ((pp = strchr (pp + 1, p))) np++;
297 np = g_test_rand_int_range (0, np) + 1;
298 pp = new - 1;
299 while (np--) pp = strchr (pp + 1, p);
300 g_assert_cmpint (*pp, ==, p)do { gint64 __n1 = (*pp), __n2 = (p); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else
g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 300, ((const char*) (__func__)), "*pp" " " "==" " " "p", (long
double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
301
302 while (*pp)
303 {
304 *pp = *(pp + 1);
305 pp++;
306 }
307
308 return new;
309 }
310
311 /* else, perform a random mutation at a random point */
312 {
313 gint length, n;
314 gchar *new;
315 gchar p;
316
317 if (randomly (0.3))
318 {
319 /* insert a paren/brace */
320 if (randomly (0.5))
321 if (randomly (0.5)) p = '('; else p = ')';
322 else
323 if (randomly (0.5)) p = '{'; else p = '}';
324 }
325 else if (randomly (0.5))
326 {
327 /* insert junk */
328 p = INVALIDS"cefjklpwz&@^$"[g_test_rand_int_range (0, N_INVALIDS((sizeof ("cefjklpwz&@^$") / sizeof (("cefjklpwz&@^$"
)[0])) - 1))];
329 }
330 else
331 {
332 /* truncate */
333 p = '\0';
334 }
335
336
337 length = strlen (type_string);
338 new = g_malloc (length + 2);
339 n = g_test_rand_int_range (0, length);
340 memcpy (new, type_string, n);
341 new[n] = p;
342 memcpy (new + n + 1, type_string + n, length - n);
343 new[length + 1] = '\0';
344
345 return new;
346 }
347}

349/* describe a type using the same language as is generated
350 * while generating the type with append_type_string
351 */
352static gchar *
353describe_type (const GVariantType *type)
354{

357 if (g_variant_type_is_container (type))

("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 359, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "g_variant_type_is_basic (type)" "' should be FALSE")

362 {

365 g_free (subtype);
366 }

369 gchar *subtype = describe_type (g_variant_type_element (type));
370 result = g_strdup_printf ("m of %s", subtype);
371 g_free (subtype);
372 }

397

399 }
400 else
401 result = g_strdup ("R");
402 }
403 else if (g_variant_type_is_dict_entry (type))

408 value = describe_type (g_variant_type_value (type));
409 key2 = describe_type (g_variant_type_first (type));
410 value2 = describe_type (

412 g_assert_null (g_variant_type_next (g_variant_type_next (do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((g_variant_type_next (g_variant_type_next ( g_variant_type_first
(type)))) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"

665/* Test that scanning a deeply recursive type string doesn’t exhaust our
666 * stack space (which it would if the type string scanner was recursive). */
667static void
668test_gvarianttype_string_scan_recursion_tuple (void)
669{
670 gchar *type_string = NULL((void*)0);
671 gsize type_string_len = 1000001; /* not including nul terminator */
672 gsize i;
673
674 /* Build a long type string of ‘((…u…))’. */
675 type_string = g_new0 (gchar, type_string_len + 1)(gchar *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (type_string_len
+ 1); gsize __s = sizeof (gchar); gpointer __p; if (__s == 1
) __p = g_malloc0 (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (__n) &&
(__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *2UL+1UL) / __s
)) __p = g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n (__n, __s
); __p; }));
676 for (i = 0; i < type_string_len; i++)
677 {
678 if (i < type_string_len / 2)
679 type_string[i] = '(';
680 else if (i == type_string_len / 2)
681 type_string[i] = 'u';
682 else
683 type_string[i] = ')';
684 }
685
686 /* Goes (way) over allowed recursion limit. */
687 g_assert_false (g_variant_type_string_is_valid (type_string))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (!(g_variant_type_string_is_valid (type_string))) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 687
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_type_string_is_valid (type_string)"
"' should be FALSE"); } while (0);
688
689 g_free (type_string);
690}

716#define ALIGNED(x, y)(((x + (y - 1)) / y) * y) (((x + (y - 1)) / y) * y)

718/* do our own calculation of the fixed_size and alignment of a type
719 * using a simple algorithm to make sure the "fancy" one in the
720 * implementation is correct.
721 */
722static void
723calculate_type_info (const GVariantType *type,
724 gsize *fixed_size,
725 guint *alignment)
726{
727 if (g_variant_type_is_array (type) ||
728 g_variant_type_is_maybe (type))
729 {
730 calculate_type_info (g_variant_type_element (type), NULL((void*)0), alignment);
731
732 if (fixed_size)
733 *fixed_size = 0;
734 }
735 else if (g_variant_type_is_tuple (type) ||
736 g_variant_type_is_dict_entry (type))
737 {
738 if (g_variant_type_n_items (type))
739 {
740 const GVariantType *sub;
741 gboolean variable;
742 gsize size;
743 guint al;
744
745 variable = FALSE(0);
746 size = 0;
747 al = 0;
748
749 sub = g_variant_type_first (type);
750 do
751 {
752 gsize this_fs;
753 guint this_al;
754
755 calculate_type_info (sub, &this_fs, &this_al);
756
757 al = MAX (al, this_al)(((al) > (this_al)) ? (al) : (this_al));
758
759 if (!this_fs)
760 {
761 variable = TRUE(!(0));
762 size = 0;
763 }
764
765 if (!variable)
766 {
767 size = ALIGNED (size, this_al)(((size + (this_al - 1)) / this_al) * this_al);
768 size += this_fs;
769 }
770 }
771 while ((sub = g_variant_type_next (sub)));
772
773 size = ALIGNED (size, al)(((size + (al - 1)) / al) * al);
774
775 if (alignment)
776 *alignment = al;
777
778 if (fixed_size)
779 *fixed_size = size;
780 }
781 else
782 {
783 if (fixed_size)
784 *fixed_size = 1;
785
786 if (alignment)
787 *alignment = 1;
788 }
789 }
790 else
791 {
792 gint fs, al;
793
794 if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_BOOLEAN((const GVariantType *) "b")) ||
795 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_BYTE((const GVariantType *) "y")))
796 {
797 al = fs = 1;
798 }
799
800 else if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT16((const GVariantType *) "n")) ||
801 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT16((const GVariantType *) "q")))
802 {
803 al = fs = 2;
804 }
805
806 else if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT32((const GVariantType *) "i")) ||
807 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT32((const GVariantType *) "u")) ||
808 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_HANDLE((const GVariantType *) "h")))
809 {
810 al = fs = 4;
811 }
812
813 else if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_INT64((const GVariantType *) "x")) ||
814 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT64((const GVariantType *) "t")) ||
815 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_DOUBLE((const GVariantType *) "d")))
816 {
817 al = fs = 8;
818 }
819 else if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_STRING((const GVariantType *) "s")) ||
820 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_OBJECT_PATH((const GVariantType *) "o")) ||
821 g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_SIGNATURE((const GVariantType *) "g")))
822 {
823 al = 1;
824 fs = 0;
825 }
826 else if (g_variant_type_equal (type, G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v")))
827 {
828 al = 8;
829 fs = 0;
830 }
831 else
832 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 832, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
833
834 if (fixed_size)
835 *fixed_size = fs;
836
837 if (alignment)
838 *alignment = al;
839 }
840}
841
842/* same as the describe_type() function above, but iterates over
843 * typeinfo instead of types.
844 */
845static gchar *
846describe_info (GVariantTypeInfo *info)
847{
848 gchar *result;
849
850 switch (g_variant_type_info_get_type_char (info)(g_variant_type_info_get_type_string(info)[0]))
851 {
852 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_MAYBE'm':
853 {
854 gchar *element;
855
856 element = describe_info (g_variant_type_info_element (info));
857 result = g_strdup_printf ("m of %s", element);
858 g_free (element);
859 }
860 break;
861
862 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_ARRAY'a':
863 {
864 gchar *element;
865
866 element = describe_info (g_variant_type_info_element (info));
867 result = g_strdup_printf ("a of %s", element);
868 g_free (element);
869 }
870 break;
871
872 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_TUPLE'(':
873 {
874 const gchar *sep = "";
875 GString *string;
876 gint length;
877 gsize i;
878
879 string = g_string_new ("t of [");
880 length = g_variant_type_info_n_members (info);
881
882 for (i = 0; i < length; i++)
883 {
884 const GVariantMemberInfo *minfo;
885 gchar *subtype;
886
887 g_string_append (string, sep);
888 sep = ", ";
889
890 minfo = g_variant_type_info_member_info (info, i);
891 subtype = describe_info (minfo->type_info);
892 g_string_append (string, subtype);
893 g_free (subtype);
894 }
895
896 g_string_append_c (string, ']')g_string_append_c_inline (string, ']');
897
898 result = g_string_free (string, FALSE(0));
899 }
900 break;
901
902 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_DICT_ENTRY'{':
903 {
904 const GVariantMemberInfo *keyinfo, *valueinfo;
905 gchar *key, *value;
906
907 g_assert_cmpint (g_variant_type_info_n_members (info), ==, 2)do { gint64 __n1 = (g_variant_type_info_n_members (info)), __n2
= (2); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum (
"GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 907, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "g_variant_type_info_n_members (info)" " " "==" " " "2", (
long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0
);
908 keyinfo = g_variant_type_info_member_info (info, 0);
909 valueinfo = g_variant_type_info_member_info (info, 1);
910 key = describe_info (keyinfo->type_info);
911 value = describe_info (valueinfo->type_info);
912 result = g_strjoin ("", "e of [", key, ", ", value, "]", NULL((void*)0));
913 g_free (key);
914 g_free (value);
915 }
916 break;
917
918 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_VARIANT'v':
919 result = g_strdup ("V");
920 break;
921
922 default:
923 result = g_strdup (g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (info));
924 g_assert_cmpint (strlen (result), ==, 1)do { gint64 __n1 = (strlen (result)), __n2 = (1); if (__n1 ==
__n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 924, ((const char*) (__func__)), "strlen (result)" " " "=="
" " "1", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i');
} while (0);
925 break;
926 }
927
928 return result;
929}
930
931/* check that the O(1) method of calculating offsets meshes with the
932 * results of simple iteration.
933 */
934static void
935check_offsets (GVariantTypeInfo *info,
936 const GVariantType *type)
937{
938 gsize flavour;
939 gint length;
940
941 length = g_variant_type_info_n_members (info);
942 g_assert_cmpint (length, ==, g_variant_type_n_items (type))do { gint64 __n1 = (length), __n2 = (g_variant_type_n_items (
type)); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum (
"GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 942, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "length" " " "==" " " "g_variant_type_n_items (type)", (long
double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
943
944 /* the 'flavour' is the low order bits of the ending point of
945 * variable-size items in the tuple. this lets us test that the type
946 * info is correct for various starting alignments.
947 */
948 for (flavour = 0; flavour < 8; flavour++)
949 {
950 const GVariantType *subtype;
951 gsize last_offset_index;
952 gsize last_offset;
953 gsize position;
954 gsize i;
955
956 subtype = g_variant_type_first (type);
957 last_offset_index = -1;
958 last_offset = 0;
959 position = 0;
960
961 /* go through the tuple, keeping track of our position */
962 for (i = 0; i < length; i++)
963 {
964 gsize fixed_size;
965 guint alignment;
966
967 calculate_type_info (subtype, &fixed_size, &alignment);
968
969 position = ALIGNED (position, alignment)(((position + (alignment - 1)) / alignment) * alignment);
970
971 /* compare our current aligned position (ie: the start of this
972 * item) to the start offset that would be calculated if we
973 * used the type info
974 */
975 {
976 const GVariantMemberInfo *member;
977 gsize start;
978
979 member = g_variant_type_info_member_info (info, i);
980 g_assert_cmpint (member->i, ==, last_offset_index)do { gint64 __n1 = (member->i), __n2 = (last_offset_index)
; if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 980, ((const char*) (__func__))
, "member->i" " " "==" " " "last_offset_index", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
981
982 /* do the calculation using the typeinfo */
983 start = last_offset;
984 start += member->a;
985 start &= member->b;
986 start |= member->c;
987
988 /* did we reach the same spot? */
989 g_assert_cmpint (start, ==, position)do { gint64 __n1 = (start), __n2 = (position); if (__n1 == __n2
) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 989, ((const char*) (__func__)), "start" " " "==" " " "position"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
990 }
991
992 if (fixed_size)
993 {
994 /* fixed size. add that size. */
995 position += fixed_size;
996 }
997 else
998 {
999 /* variable size. do the flavouring. */
1000 while ((position & 0x7) != flavour)
1001 position++;
1002
1003 /* and store the offset, just like it would be in the
1004 * serialised data.
1005 */
1006 last_offset = position;
1007 last_offset_index++;
1008 }
1009
1010 /* next type */
1011 subtype = g_variant_type_next (subtype);
1012 }
1013
1014 /* make sure we used up exactly all the types */
1015 g_assert_null (subtype)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((subtype) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1015, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "subtype" "' should be NULL"); } while (0);
1016 }
1017}
1018
1019static void
1020test_gvarianttypeinfo (void)
1021{
1022 gsize i;
1023
1024 for (i = 0; i < 2000; i++)
1025 {
1026 GString *type_string, *description;
1027 gsize fixed_size1, fixed_size2;
1028 guint alignment1, alignment2;
1029 GVariantTypeInfo *info;
1030 GVariantType *type;
1031 gchar *desc;
1032
1033 type_string = g_string_new (NULL((void*)0));
1034 description = g_string_new (NULL((void*)0));
1035
1036 /* random type */
1037 type = append_type_string (type_string, description, TRUE(!(0)), 6);
1038
1039 /* create a typeinfo for it */
1040 info = g_variant_type_info_get (type);
1041
1042 /* make sure the typeinfo has the right type string */
1043 g_assert_cmpstr (g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (info), ==,do { const char *__s1 = (g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (
info)), *__s2 = (type_string->str); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2
) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1044, ((const char*) (__func__)), "g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (info)"
" " "==" " " "type_string->str", __s1, "==", __s2); } while
(0)
1044 type_string->str)do { const char *__s1 = (g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (
info)), *__s2 = (type_string->str); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2
) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1044, ((const char*) (__func__)), "g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (info)"
" " "==" " " "type_string->str", __s1, "==", __s2); } while
(0);
1045
1046 /* calculate the alignment and fixed size, compare to the
1047 * typeinfo's calculations
1048 */
1049 calculate_type_info (type, &fixed_size1, &alignment1);
1050 g_variant_type_info_query (info, &alignment2, &fixed_size2);
1051 g_assert_cmpint (fixed_size1, ==, fixed_size2)do { gint64 __n1 = (fixed_size1), __n2 = (fixed_size2); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1051, ((const char*) (__func__)), "fixed_size1" " " "==" " "
"fixed_size2", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2,
'i'); } while (0);
1052 g_assert_cmpint (alignment1, ==, alignment2 + 1)do { gint64 __n1 = (alignment1), __n2 = (alignment2 + 1); if (
__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1052, ((const char*) (__func__)), "alignment1" " " "==" " "
"alignment2 + 1", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2
, 'i'); } while (0);
1053
1054 /* test the iteration functions over typeinfo structures by
1055 * "describing" the typeinfo and verifying equality.
1056 */
1057 desc = describe_info (info);
1058 g_assert_cmpstr (desc, ==, description->str)do { const char *__s1 = (desc), *__s2 = (description->str)
; if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1058, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "desc" " " "==" " " "description->str", __s1, "==", __s2
); } while (0);
1059
1060 /* do extra checks for containers */
1061 if (g_variant_type_is_array (type) ||
1062 g_variant_type_is_maybe (type))
1063 {
1064 const GVariantType *element;
1065 gsize efs1, efs2;
1066 guint ea1, ea2;
1067
1068 element = g_variant_type_element (type);
1069 calculate_type_info (element, &efs1, &ea1);
1070 g_variant_type_info_query_element (info, &ea2, &efs2);
1071 g_assert_cmpint (efs1, ==, efs2)do { gint64 __n1 = (efs1), __n2 = (efs2); if (__n1 == __n2) ;
else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1071, ((const char*) (__func__)), "efs1" " " "==" " " "efs2"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1072 g_assert_cmpint (ea1, ==, ea2 + 1)do { gint64 __n1 = (ea1), __n2 = (ea2 + 1); if (__n1 == __n2)
; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1072, ((const char*) (__func__)), "ea1" " " "==" " " "ea2 + 1"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1073
1074 g_assert_cmpint (ea1, ==, alignment1)do { gint64 __n1 = (ea1), __n2 = (alignment1); if (__n1 == __n2
) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1074, ((const char*) (__func__)), "ea1" " " "==" " " "alignment1"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1075 g_assert_cmpint (0, ==, fixed_size1)do { gint64 __n1 = (0), __n2 = (fixed_size1); if (__n1 == __n2
) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1075, ((const char*) (__func__)), "0" " " "==" " " "fixed_size1"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1076 }
1077 else if (g_variant_type_is_tuple (type) ||
1078 g_variant_type_is_dict_entry (type))
1079 {
1080 /* make sure the "magic constants" are working */
1081 check_offsets (info, type);
1082 }
1083
1084 g_string_free (type_string, TRUE(!(0)));
1085 g_string_free (description, TRUE(!(0)));
1086 g_variant_type_info_unref (info);
1087 g_variant_type_free (type);
1088 g_free (desc);
1089 }
1090
1091 g_variant_type_info_assert_no_infos ();
1092}
1093
1094#define MAX_FIXED_MULTIPLIER256 256
1095#define MAX_INSTANCE_SIZE1024 1024
1096#define MAX_ARRAY_CHILDREN128 128
1097#define MAX_TUPLE_CHILDREN128 128
1098
1099/* this function generates a random type such that all characteristics
1100 * that are "interesting" to the serialiser are tested.
1101 *
1102 * this basically means:
1103 * - test different alignments
1104 * - test variable sized items and fixed sized items
1105 * - test different fixed sizes
1106 */
1107static gchar *
1108random_type_string (void)
1109{
1110 const guchar base_types[] = "ynix";
1111 guchar base_type;
1112
1113 base_type = base_types[g_test_rand_int_range (0, 4)];
1114
1115 if (g_test_rand_bit ()(0 != (g_test_rand_int() & (1 << 15))))
1116 /* construct a fixed-sized type */
1117 {
1118 char type_string[MAX_FIXED_MULTIPLIER256];
1119 guint multiplier;
1120 gsize i = 0;
1121
1122 multiplier = g_test_rand_int_range (1, sizeof type_string - 1);
1123
1124 type_string[i++] = '(';
1125 while (multiplier--)
1126 type_string[i++] = base_type;
1127 type_string[i++] = ')';
1128
1129 return g_strndup (type_string, i);
1130 }
1131 else
1132 /* construct a variable-sized type */
1133 {
1134 char type_string[2] = { 'a', base_type };
1135
1136 return g_strndup (type_string, 2);
1137 }
1138}
1139
1140typedef struct
1141{
1142 GVariantTypeInfo *type_info;
1143 guint alignment;
1144 gsize size;
1145 gboolean is_fixed_sized;
1146
1147 guint32 seed;
1148
1149#define INSTANCE_MAGIC1287582829 1287582829
1150 guint magic;
1151} RandomInstance;
1152
1153static RandomInstance *
1154random_instance (GVariantTypeInfo *type_info)
1155{
1156 RandomInstance *instance;
1157
1158 instance = g_slice_new (RandomInstance)((RandomInstance*) g_slice_alloc (sizeof (RandomInstance)));
1159
1160 if (type_info == NULL((void*)0))
1161 {
1162 gchar *str = random_type_string ();
1163 instance->type_info = g_variant_type_info_get (G_VARIANT_TYPE (str)(g_variant_type_checked_ ((str))));
1164 g_free (str);
1165 }
1166 else
1167 instance->type_info = g_variant_type_info_ref (type_info);
1168
1169 instance->seed = g_test_rand_int ();
1170
1171 g_variant_type_info_query (instance->type_info,
1172 &instance->alignment,
1173 &instance->size);
1174
1175 instance->is_fixed_sized = instance->size != 0;
1176
1177 if (!instance->is_fixed_sized)
1178 instance->size = g_test_rand_int_range (0, MAX_INSTANCE_SIZE1024);
1179
1180 instance->magic = INSTANCE_MAGIC1287582829;
1181
1182 return instance;
1183}

1185static void
1186random_instance_free (RandomInstance *instance)
1187{
1188 g_variant_type_info_unref (instance->type_info);
1189 g_slice_free (RandomInstance, instance)do { if (1) g_slice_free1 (sizeof (RandomInstance), (instance
)); else (void) ((RandomInstance*) 0 == (instance)); } while (
0);
1190}

1192static void
1193append_instance_size (RandomInstance *instance,
1194 gsize *offset)
1195{
1196 *offset += (-*offset) & instance->alignment;
1197 *offset += instance->size;
1198}

1200static void
1201random_instance_write (RandomInstance *instance,
1202 guchar *buffer)
1203{
1204 GRand *rand;
1205 gsize i;
1206
1207 g_assert_cmpint ((gsize) buffer & ALIGN_BITS & instance->alignment, ==, 0)do { gint64 __n1 = ((gsize) buffer & (sizeof (struct { char
a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble z; } b; }) - 9) &
instance->alignment), __n2 = (0); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else
g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1207, ((const char*) (__func__)), "(gsize) buffer & ALIGN_BITS & instance->alignment"
" " "==" " " "0", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2
, 'i'); } while (0);
1208
1209 rand = g_rand_new_with_seed (instance->seed);
1210 for (i = 0; i < instance->size; i++)
1211 buffer[i] = g_rand_int (rand);

1215static void
1216append_instance_data (RandomInstance *instance,
1217 guchar **buffer)
1218{

1220 *(*buffer)++ = '\0';
1221
1222 random_instance_write (instance, *buffer);
1223 *buffer += instance->size;

1226static gboolean

, 1234, ((const char*) (__func__)), "(gsize) buffer & ALIGN_BITS & instance->alignment"
" " "==" " " "0", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2
, 'i'); } while (0);
1235 g_assert_cmpint (size, ==, instance->size)do { gint64 __n1 = (size), __n2 = (instance->size); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1235, ((const char*) (__func__)), "size" " " "==" " " "instance->size"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);

) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"

, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);

1248
1249static gboolean
1250random_instance_check (RandomInstance *instance,
1251 guchar *buffer,
1252 gsize size)
1253{
1254 GRand *rand;
1255 gsize i;
1256
1257 g_assert_cmpint ((gsize) buffer & ALIGN_BITS & instance->alignment, ==, 0)do { gint64 __n1 = ((gsize) buffer & (sizeof (struct { char
a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble z; } b; }) - 9) &
instance->alignment), __n2 = (0); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else
g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1257, ((const char*) (__func__)), "(gsize) buffer & ALIGN_BITS & instance->alignment"
" " "==" " " "0", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2
, 'i'); } while (0);
1258
1259 if (size != instance->size)
1260 return FALSE(0);
1261
1262 rand = g_rand_new_with_seed (instance->seed);
1263 for (i = 0; i < instance->size; i++)
1264 if (buffer[i] != (guchar) g_rand_int (rand))
1265 break;
1266 g_rand_free (rand);
1267
1268 return i == instance->size;
1269}
1270
1271static void
1272random_instance_filler (GVariantSerialised *serialised,
1273 gpointer data)
1274{
1275 RandomInstance *instance = data;
1276
1277 g_assert_cmpuint (instance->magic, ==, INSTANCE_MAGIC)do { guint64 __n1 = (instance->magic), __n2 = (1287582829)
; if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1277, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "instance->magic" " " "==" " " "INSTANCE_MAGIC", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
1278
1279 if (serialised->type_info == NULL((void*)0))
1280 serialised->type_info = instance->type_info;
1281
1282 if (serialised->size == 0)
1283 serialised->size = instance->size;
1284
1285 serialised->depth = 0;
1286
1287 g_assert_true (serialised->type_info == instance->type_info)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (serialised->type_info == instance->type_info) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1287
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "serialised->type_info == instance->type_info"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
1288 g_assert_cmpuint (serialised->size, ==, instance->size)do { guint64 __n1 = (serialised->size), __n2 = (instance->
size); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1288, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "serialised->size" " " "==" " " "instance->size", (long
double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
1289
1290 if (serialised->data)
1291 random_instance_write (instance, serialised->data);
1292}
1293
1294static gsize
1295calculate_offset_size (gsize body_size,
1296 gsize n_offsets)
1297{
1298 if (body_size == 0)
1299 return 0;
1300
1301 if (body_size + n_offsets <= G_MAXUINT8((guint8) 0xff))
1302 return 1;
1303
1304 if (body_size + 2 * n_offsets <= G_MAXUINT16((guint16) 0xffff))
1305 return 2;
1306
1307 if (body_size + 4 * n_offsets <= G_MAXUINT32((guint32) 0xffffffff))
1308 return 4;
1309
1310 /* the test case won't generate anything bigger */
1311 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1311, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
1312}
1313
1314static gpointer
1315flavoured_malloc (gsize size, gsize flavour)
1316{
1317 g_assert_cmpuint (flavour, <, 8)do { guint64 __n1 = (flavour), __n2 = (8); if (__n1 < __n2
) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1317, ((const char*) (__func__)), "flavour" " " "<" " " "8"
, (long double) __n1, "<", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1318
1319 if (size == 0)
1320 return NULL((void*)0);
1321
1322 return ((gchar *) g_malloc (size + flavour)) + flavour;
1323}
1324
1325static void
1326flavoured_free (gpointer data,
1327 gsize flavour)
1328{
1329 if (!data)
1330 return;
1331 g_free (((gchar *) data) - flavour);
1332}
1333
1334static gpointer
1335align_malloc (gsize size)
1336{
1337 gpointer mem;
1338
1339#ifdef HAVE_POSIX_MEMALIGN1
1340 if (posix_memalign (&mem, 8, size))
1341 g_error ("posix_memalign failed");
1342#else
1343 /* NOTE: there may be platforms that lack posix_memalign() and also
1344 * have malloc() that returns non-8-aligned. if so, we need to try
1345 * harder here.
1346 */
1347 mem = malloc (size);
1348#endif
1349
1350 return mem;
1351}
1352
1353static void
1354align_free (gpointer mem)
1355{
1356 free (mem);
1357}
1358
1359static void
1360append_offset (guchar **offset_ptr,
1361 gsize offset,
1362 guint offset_size)
1363{
1364 union
1365 {
1366 guchar bytes[sizeof (gsize)];
1367 gsize integer;
1368 } tmpvalue;
1369
1370 tmpvalue.integer = GSIZE_TO_LE (offset)((gsize) ((guint64) (offset)));
1371 memcpy (*offset_ptr, tmpvalue.bytes, offset_size);
1372 *offset_ptr += offset_size;
1373}
1374
1375static void
1376prepend_offset (guchar **offset_ptr,
1377 gsize offset,
1378 guint offset_size)
1379{
1380 union
1381 {
1382 guchar bytes[sizeof (gsize)];
1383 gsize integer;
1384 } tmpvalue;
1385
1386 *offset_ptr -= offset_size;
1387 tmpvalue.integer = GSIZE_TO_LE (offset)((gsize) ((guint64) (offset)));
1388 memcpy (*offset_ptr, tmpvalue.bytes, offset_size);
1389}

1391static void
1392test_maybe (void)
1393{
1394 GVariantTypeInfo *type_info;
1395 RandomInstance *instance;
1396 gsize needed_size;
1397 guchar *data;
1398
1399 instance = random_instance (NULL((void*)0));
1400
1401 {
1402 const gchar *element;
1403 gchar *tmp;
1404
1405 element = g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (instance->type_info);
1406 tmp = g_strdup_printf ("m%s", element);
1407 type_info = g_variant_type_info_get (G_VARIANT_TYPE (tmp)(g_variant_type_checked_ ((tmp))));
1408 g_free (tmp);
1409 }
1410
1411 needed_size = g_variant_serialiser_needed_size (type_info,
1412 random_instance_filler,
1413 NULL((void*)0), 0);
1414 g_assert_cmpint (needed_size, ==, 0)do { gint64 __n1 = (needed_size), __n2 = (0); if (__n1 == __n2
) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1414, ((const char*) (__func__)), "needed_size" " " "==" " "
"0", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1415
1416 needed_size = g_variant_serialiser_needed_size (type_info,
1417 random_instance_filler,
1418 (gpointer *) &instance, 1);
1419
1420 if (instance->is_fixed_sized)
1421 g_assert_cmpint (needed_size, ==, instance->size)do { gint64 __n1 = (needed_size), __n2 = (instance->size);
if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib",
"../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1421, ((const char*) (__func__))
, "needed_size" " " "==" " " "instance->size", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
1422 else
1423 g_assert_cmpint (needed_size, ==, instance->size + 1)do { gint64 __n1 = (needed_size), __n2 = (instance->size +
1); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1423, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "needed_size" " " "==" " " "instance->size + 1", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
1424
1425 {
1426 guchar *ptr;
1427
1428 ptr = data = align_malloc (needed_size);
1429 append_instance_data (instance, &ptr);
1430
1431 if (!instance->is_fixed_sized)
1432 *ptr++ = '\0';
1433
1434 g_assert_cmpint (ptr - data, ==, needed_size)do { gint64 __n1 = (ptr - data), __n2 = (needed_size); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 1434, ((const char*) (__func__)), "ptr - data" " " "==" " "
"needed_size", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2,
'i'); } while (0);
1435 }
1436
1437 {
1438 guint alignment;
1439 gsize flavour;
1440
1441 alignment = (instance->alignment & ALIGN_BITS(sizeof (struct { char a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble
z; } b; }) - 9)) + 1;
1442
1443 for (flavour = 0; flavour < 8; flavour += alignment)
1444 {
1445 GVariantSerialised serialised;
1446 GVariantSerialised child;
1447
1448 serialised.type_info = type_info;
1449 serialised.data = flavoured_malloc (needed_size, flavour);
1450 serialised.size = needed_size;
1451 serialised.depth = 0;
1452
1453 g_variant_serialiser_serialise (serialised,
1454 random_instance_filler,
1455 (gpointer *) &instance, 1);
1456 child = g_variant_serialised_get_child (serialised, 0);
1457 g_assert_true (child.type_info == instance->type_info)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (child.type_info == instance->type_info) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1457
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "child.type_info == instance->type_info"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
1458 random_instance_assert (instance, child.data, child.size);
1459 g_variant_type_info_unref (child.type_info);
1460 flavoured_free (serialised.data, flavour);
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 g_variant_type_info_unref (type_info);
1465 random_instance_free (instance);
1466 align_free (data);
1467}

(0);
1540 }

; if (body_ptr == data + needed_size - offset_size * n_children

; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"

("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1556, ((const char*) (__func__

1622static void
1623test_tuple (void)
1624{
1625 GVariantTypeInfo *type_info;
1626 RandomInstance **instances;
1627 gboolean fixed_size;
1628 gsize needed_size;
1629 gsize offset_size;
1630 guint n_children;
1631 guint alignment;
1632 guchar *data;
1633
1634 n_children = g_test_rand_int_range (0, MAX_TUPLE_CHILDREN128);
1635 instances = g_new (RandomInstance *, n_children)(RandomInstance * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (n_children
); gsize __s = sizeof (RandomInstance *); gpointer __p; if (__s
== 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (__n
) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *2UL
+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
1636
1637 {
1638 GString *type_string;
1639 gsize i;
1640
1641 fixed_size = TRUE(!(0));
1642 alignment = 0;
1643
1644 type_string = g_string_new ("(");
1645 for (i = 0; i < n_children; i++)
1646 {
1647 const gchar *str;
1648
1649 instances[i] = random_instance (NULL((void*)0));
1650
1651 alignment |= instances[i]->alignment;
1652 if (!instances[i]->is_fixed_sized)
1653 fixed_size = FALSE(0);
1654
1655 str = g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (instances[i]->type_info);
1656 g_string_append (type_string, str);
1657 }
1658 g_string_append_c (type_string, ')')g_string_append_c_inline (type_string, ')');
1659
1660 type_info = g_variant_type_info_get (G_VARIANT_TYPE (type_string->str)(g_variant_type_checked_ ((type_string->str))));
1661 g_string_free (type_string, TRUE(!(0)));
1662 }
1663
1664 needed_size = g_variant_serialiser_needed_size (type_info,
1665 random_instance_filler,
1666 (gpointer *) instances,
1667 n_children);
1668 {
1669 gsize body_size = 0;
1670 gsize offsets = 0;
1671 gsize i;
1672
1673 for (i = 0; i < n_children; i++)
1674 {
1675 append_instance_size (instances[i], &body_size);
1676
1677 if (i != n_children - 1 && !instances[i]->is_fixed_sized)
1678 offsets++;
1679 }
1680
1681 if (fixed_size)
1682 {
1683 body_size += (-body_size) & alignment;
1684
1685 g_assert_true ((body_size == 0) == (n_children == 0))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((body_size == 0) == (n_children == 0)) _g_boolean_var_ =
1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1685
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "(body_size == 0) == (n_children == 0)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
1686 if (n_children == 0)
1687 body_size = 1;
1688 }
1689
1690 offset_size = calculate_offset_size (body_size, offsets);
1691 g_assert_cmpint (needed_size, ==, body_size + offsets * offset_size)do { gint64 __n1 = (needed_size), __n2 = (body_size + offsets
* offset_size); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1691, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "needed_size" " " "==" " " "body_size + offsets * offset_size"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
1692 }
1693
1694 {
1695 guchar *body_ptr;
1696 guchar *ofs_ptr;
1697 gsize i;
1698
1699 body_ptr = data = align_malloc (needed_size);
1700 ofs_ptr = body_ptr + needed_size;
1701
1702 for (i = 0; i < n_children; i++)
1703 {
1704 append_instance_data (instances[i], &body_ptr);
1705
1706 if (i != n_children - 1 && !instances[i]->is_fixed_sized)
1707 prepend_offset (&ofs_ptr, body_ptr - data, offset_size);
1708 }
1709
1710 if (fixed_size)
1711 {
1712 while (((gsize) body_ptr) & alignment)
1713 *body_ptr++ = '\0';
1714
1715 g_assert_true ((body_ptr == data) == (n_children == 0))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((body_ptr == data) == (n_children == 0)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1715
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "(body_ptr == data) == (n_children == 0)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
1716 if (n_children == 0)
1717 *body_ptr++ = '\0';
1718
1719 }
1720
1721
1722 g_assert_true (body_ptr == ofs_ptr)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (body_ptr == ofs_ptr) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_

, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1722, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "body_ptr == ofs_ptr" "' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
1723 }
1724
1725 {
1726 gsize flavour;
1727 gsize i;
1728
1729 alignment = (alignment & ALIGN_BITS(sizeof (struct { char a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble
z; } b; }) - 9)) + 1;
1730

1732 {
1733 GVariantSerialised serialised;
1734
1735 serialised.type_info = type_info;
1736 serialised.data = flavoured_malloc (needed_size, flavour);
1737 serialised.size = needed_size;
1738 serialised.depth = 0;

1747

; if (child.type_info == instances[i]->type_info) _g_boolean_var_

1759 }

1785static void
1786test_variant (void)
1787{
1788 GVariantTypeInfo *type_info;
1789 RandomInstance *instance;
1790 const gchar *type_string;
1791 gsize needed_size;
1792 guchar *data;
1793 gsize len;
1794
1795 type_info = g_variant_type_info_get (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"));
1796 instance = random_instance (NULL((void*)0));
1797
1798 type_string = g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (instance->type_info);
1799 len = strlen (type_string);
1800

1802 random_instance_filler,
1803 (gpointer *) &instance, 1);

= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 1816, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "data + needed_size == ptr" "' should be TRUE"); } while
(0);
1817 }
1818
1819 {
1820 gsize alignment;
1821 gsize flavour;
1822
1823 /* variants are always 8-aligned */
1824 alignment = ALIGN_BITS(sizeof (struct { char a; union { guint64 x; void *y; gdouble
z; } b; }) - 9) + 1;
1825
1826 for (flavour = 0; flavour < 8; flavour += alignment)
1827 {
1828 GVariantSerialised serialised;

1830
1831 serialised.type_info = type_info;

1833 serialised.size = needed_size;
1834 serialised.depth = 0;
1835

1837 (gpointer *) &instance, 1);
1838

} while (0);
1841

)), __n2 = (1); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum

(0);

1934
1935typedef struct _TreeInstance TreeInstance;
1936struct _TreeInstance
1937{
1938 GVariantTypeInfo *info;
1939
1940 TreeInstance **children;
1941 gsize n_children;
1942
1943 union {
1944 guint64 integer;
1945 gdouble floating;
1946 gchar string[200];
1947 } data;
1948 gsize data_size;
1949};
1950
1951static GVariantType *
1952make_random_definite_type (int depth)
1953{
1954 GString *description;
1955 GString *type_string;
1956 GVariantType *type;
1957
1958 description = g_string_new (NULL((void*)0));
1959 type_string = g_string_new (NULL((void*)0));
1960 type = append_type_string (type_string, description, TRUE(!(0)), depth);
1961 g_string_free (description, TRUE(!(0)));
1962 g_string_free (type_string, TRUE(!(0)));
1963
1964 return type;
1965}
1966
1967static void
1968make_random_string (gchar *string,
1969 gsize size,
1970 const GVariantType *type)
1971{
1972 gsize i;
1973
1974 /* create strings that are valid signature strings */
1975#define good_chars "bynqiuxthdsog"
1976
1977 for (i = 0; i < size - 1; i++)
1978 string[i] = good_chars[g_test_rand_int_range (0, strlen (good_chars))];
1979 string[i] = '\0';
1980
1981 /* in case we need an object path, prefix a '/' */
1982 if (*g_variant_type_peek_string (type) == 'o')
1983 string[0] = '/';
1984
1985#undef good_chars
1986}
1987
1988static TreeInstance *
1989tree_instance_new (const GVariantType *type,
1990 int depth)
1991{
1992 const GVariantType *child_type = NULL((void*)0);
1993 GVariantType *mytype = NULL((void*)0);
1994 TreeInstance *instance;
1995 gboolean is_tuple_type;
1996
1997 if (type == NULL((void*)0))
1998 type = mytype = make_random_definite_type (depth);
1999
2000 instance = g_slice_new (TreeInstance)((TreeInstance*) g_slice_alloc (sizeof (TreeInstance)));
2001 instance->info = g_variant_type_info_get (type);
2002 instance->children = NULL((void*)0);
2003 instance->n_children = 0;
2004 instance->data_size = 0;
2005
2006 is_tuple_type = FALSE(0);
2007
2008 switch (*g_variant_type_peek_string (type))
2009 {
2010 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_MAYBE'm':
2011 instance->n_children = g_test_rand_int_range (0, 2);
2012 child_type = g_variant_type_element (type);
2013 break;
2014
2015 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_ARRAY'a':
2016 instance->n_children = g_test_rand_int_range (0, MAX_ARRAY_CHILDREN128);
2017 child_type = g_variant_type_element (type);
2018 break;
2019
2020 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_DICT_ENTRY'{':
2021 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_TUPLE'(':
2022 instance->n_children = g_variant_type_n_items (type);
2023 child_type = g_variant_type_first (type);
2024 is_tuple_type = TRUE(!(0));
2025 break;
2026
2027 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_VARIANT'v':
2028 instance->n_children = 1;
2029 child_type = NULL((void*)0);
2030 break;
2031
2032 case 'b':
2033 instance->data.integer = g_test_rand_int_range (0, 2);
2034 instance->data_size = 1;
2035 break;
2036
2037 case 'y':
2038 instance->data.integer = g_test_rand_int ();
2039 instance->data_size = 1;
2040 break;
2041
2042 case 'n': case 'q':
2043 instance->data.integer = g_test_rand_int ();
2044 instance->data_size = 2;
2045 break;
2046
2047 case 'i': case 'u': case 'h':
2048 instance->data.integer = g_test_rand_int ();
2049 instance->data_size = 4;
2050 break;
2051
2052 case 'x': case 't':
2053 instance->data.integer = g_test_rand_int ();
2054 instance->data.integer <<= 32;
2055 instance->data.integer |= (guint32) g_test_rand_int ();
2056 instance->data_size = 8;
2057 break;
2058
2059 case 'd':
2060 instance->data.floating = g_test_rand_double ();
2061 instance->data_size = 8;
2062 break;
2063
2064 case 's': case 'o': case 'g':
2065 instance->data_size = g_test_rand_int_range (10, 200);
2066 make_random_string (instance->data.string, instance->data_size, type);
2067 break;
2068 }
2069
2070 if (instance->data_size == 0)
2071 /* no data -> it is a container */
2072 {
2073 gsize i;
2074
2075 instance->children = g_new (TreeInstance *, instance->n_children)(TreeInstance * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (instance
->n_children); gsize __s = sizeof (TreeInstance *); gpointer
__p; if (__s == 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
2076
2077 for (i = 0; i < instance->n_children; i++)
2078 {
2079 instance->children[i] = tree_instance_new (child_type, depth - 1);
2080
2081 if (is_tuple_type)
2082 child_type = g_variant_type_next (child_type);
2083 }
2084
2085 g_assert_true (!is_tuple_type || child_type == NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (!is_tuple_type || child_type == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2085
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "!is_tuple_type || child_type == NULL"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2086 }
2087
2088 g_variant_type_free (mytype);
2089
2090 return instance;
2091}

2093static void
2094tree_instance_free (TreeInstance *instance)
2095{
2096 gsize i;
2097
2098 g_variant_type_info_unref (instance->info);
2099 for (i = 0; i < instance->n_children; i++)
2100 tree_instance_free (instance->children[i]);
2101 g_free (instance->children);
2102 g_slice_free (TreeInstance, instance)do { if (1) g_slice_free1 (sizeof (TreeInstance), (instance))
; else (void) ((TreeInstance*) 0 == (instance)); } while (0);
2103}
2104
2105static gboolean i_am_writing_byteswapped;
2106
2107static void
2108tree_filler (GVariantSerialised *serialised,
2109 gpointer data)
2110{
2111 TreeInstance *instance = data;
2112
2113 if (serialised->type_info == NULL((void*)0))
2114 serialised->type_info = instance->info;
2115
2116 serialised->depth = 0;
2117
2118 if (instance->data_size == 0)
2119 /* is a container */
2120 {
2121 if (serialised->size == 0)
2122 serialised->size =
2123 g_variant_serialiser_needed_size (instance->info, tree_filler,
2124 (gpointer *) instance->children,
2125 instance->n_children);
2126
2127 if (serialised->data)
2128 g_variant_serialiser_serialise (*serialised, tree_filler,
2129 (gpointer *) instance->children,
2130 instance->n_children);
2131 }
2132 else
2133 /* it is a leaf */
2134 {
2135 if (serialised->size == 0)
2136 serialised->size = instance->data_size;
2137
2138 if (serialised->data)
2139 {
2140 switch (instance->data_size)
2141 {
2142 case 1:
2143 *serialised->data = instance->data.integer;
2144 break;
2145
2146 case 2:
2147 {
2148 guint16 value = instance->data.integer;
2149
2150 if (i_am_writing_byteswapped)
2151 value = GUINT16_SWAP_LE_BE (value)(((guint16) ( (guint16) ((guint16) (value) >> 8) | (guint16
) ((guint16) (value) << 8))));
2152
2153 *(guint16 *) serialised->data = value;
2154 }
2155 break;
2156
2157 case 4:
2158 {
2159 guint32 value = instance->data.integer;
2160
2161 if (i_am_writing_byteswapped)
2162 value = GUINT32_SWAP_LE_BE (value)((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) (value)); if
(__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint32) ( (((guint32) (
__x) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) << 24) | (((guint32) (
__x) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) << 8) | (((guint32) (
__x) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >> 8) | (((guint32) (
__x) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >> 24))); else __asm__
("bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v; })));
2163
2164 *(guint32 *) serialised->data = value;
2165 }
2166 break;
2167
2168 case 8:
2169 {
2170 guint64 value = instance->data.integer;
2171
2172 if (i_am_writing_byteswapped)
2173 value = GUINT64_SWAP_LE_BE (value)((__extension__ ({ guint64 __v, __x = ((guint64) (value)); if
(__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint64) ( (((guint64) (
__x) & (guint64) (0x00000000000000ffUL)) << 56) | (
((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000000000ff00UL)) <<
40) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000000000ff0000UL
)) << 24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00000000ff000000UL
)) << 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000ff00000000UL
)) >> 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000ff0000000000UL
)) >> 24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00ff000000000000UL
)) >> 40) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0xff00000000000000UL
)) >> 56))); else __asm__ ("bswapq %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0"
(__x)); __v; })));
2174
2175 *(guint64 *) serialised->data = value;
2176 }
2177 break;
2178
2179 default:
2180 memcpy (serialised->data,
2181 instance->data.string,
2182 instance->data_size);
2183 break;
2184 }
2185 }
2186 }
2187}
2188
2189static gboolean
2190check_tree (TreeInstance *instance,
2191 GVariantSerialised serialised)
2192{
2193 if (instance->info != serialised.type_info)
2194 return FALSE(0);
2195
2196 if (instance->data_size == 0)
2197 /* is a container */
2198 {
2199 gsize i;
2200
2201 if (g_variant_serialised_n_children (serialised) !=
2202 instance->n_children)
2203 return FALSE(0);
2204
2205 for (i = 0; i < instance->n_children; i++)
2206 {
2207 GVariantSerialised child;
2208 gpointer data = NULL((void*)0);
2209 gboolean ok;
2210
2211 child = g_variant_serialised_get_child (serialised, i);
2212 if (child.size && child.data == NULL((void*)0))
2213 child.data = data = g_malloc0 (child.size);
2214 ok = check_tree (instance->children[i], child);
2215 g_variant_type_info_unref (child.type_info);
2216 g_free (data);
2217
2218 if (!ok)
2219 return FALSE(0);
2220 }
2221
2222 return TRUE(!(0));
2223 }
2224 else
2225 /* it is a leaf */
2226 {
2227 switch (instance->data_size)
2228 {
2229 case 1:
2230 g_assert_cmpuint (serialised.size, ==, 1)do { guint64 __n1 = (serialised.size), __n2 = (1); if (__n1 ==
__n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2230, ((const char*) (__func__)), "serialised.size" " " "=="
" " "1", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i');
} while (0);
2231 return *(guint8 *) serialised.data ==
2232 (guint8) instance->data.integer;
2233
2234 case 2:
2235 g_assert_cmpuint (serialised.size, ==, 2)do { guint64 __n1 = (serialised.size), __n2 = (2); if (__n1 ==
__n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2235, ((const char*) (__func__)), "serialised.size" " " "=="
" " "2", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i');
} while (0);
2236 return *(guint16 *) serialised.data ==
2237 (guint16) instance->data.integer;
2238
2239 case 4:
2240 g_assert_cmpuint (serialised.size, ==, 4)do { guint64 __n1 = (serialised.size), __n2 = (4); if (__n1 ==
__n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2240, ((const char*) (__func__)), "serialised.size" " " "=="
" " "4", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i');
} while (0);
2241 return *(guint32 *) serialised.data ==
2242 (guint32) instance->data.integer;
2243
2244 case 8:
2245 g_assert_cmpuint (serialised.size, ==, 8)do { guint64 __n1 = (serialised.size), __n2 = (8); if (__n1 ==
__n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2245, ((const char*) (__func__)), "serialised.size" " " "=="
" " "8", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i');
} while (0);
2246 return *(guint64 *) serialised.data ==
2247 (guint64) instance->data.integer;
2248
2249 default:
2250 if (serialised.size != instance->data_size)
2251 return FALSE(0);
2252
2253 return memcmp (serialised.data,
2254 instance->data.string,
2255 instance->data_size) == 0;
2256 }
2257 }
2258}

2261serialise_tree (TreeInstance *tree,
2262 GVariantSerialised *serialised)
2263{
2264 GVariantSerialised empty = {0, };
2265
2266 *serialised = empty;
2267 tree_filler (serialised, tree);

2269 tree_filler (serialised, tree);
2270}

2272static void
2273test_byteswap (void)
2274{
2275 GVariantSerialised one, two;
2276 TreeInstance *tree;
2277
2278 tree = tree_instance_new (NULL((void*)0), 3);
2279 serialise_tree (tree, &one);
2280
2281 i_am_writing_byteswapped = TRUE(!(0));
2282 serialise_tree (tree, &two);
2283 i_am_writing_byteswapped = FALSE(0);
2284
2285 g_variant_serialised_byteswap (two);
2286
2287 g_assert_cmpmem (one.data, one.size, two.data, two.size)do { gconstpointer __m1 = one.data, __m2 = two.data; int __l1
= one.size, __l2 = two.size; if (__l1 != 0 && __m1 ==
((void*)0)) g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2287, ((const char*) (__func__)), "assertion failed (" "one.size"
" == 0 || " "one.data" " != NULL)"); else if (__l2 != 0 &&
__m2 == ((void*)0)) g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2287, ((const char*) (__func__)), "assertion failed (" "two.size"
" == 0 || " "two.data" " != NULL)"); else if (__l1 != __l2) g_assertion_message_cmpnum
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2287, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "one.size" " (len(" "one.data" ")) == " "two.size" " (len("
"two.data" "))", (long double) __l1, "==", (long double) __l2
, 'i'); else if (__l1 != 0 && __m2 != ((void*)0) &&
memcmp (__m1, __m2, __l1) != 0) g_assertion_message ("GLib",
"../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2287, ((const char*) (__func__))
, "assertion failed (" "one.data" " == " "two.data" ")"); } while
(0);
2288 g_assert_cmpuint (one.depth, ==, two.depth)do { guint64 __n1 = (one.depth), __n2 = (two.depth); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2288, ((const char*) (__func__)), "one.depth" " " "==" " " "two.depth"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
2289
2290 tree_instance_free (tree);
2291 g_free (one.data);
2292 g_free (two.data);
2293}

2305
2306static void
2307test_serialiser_children (void)
2308{
2309 GBytes *data1, *data2;
2310 GVariant *child1, *child2;
2311 GVariantType *mv_type = g_variant_type_new_maybe (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"));
2312 GVariant *variant, *child;
2313
2314 g_test_bug ("https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/issues/1865");
2315 g_test_summary ("Test that getting a child variant before and after "
2316 "serialisation of the parent works");
2317
2318 /* Construct a variable sized array containing a child which serialises to a
2319 * zero-length bytestring. */
2320 child = g_variant_new_maybe (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"), NULL((void*)0));
2321 variant = g_variant_new_array (mv_type, &child, 1);
2322
2323 /* Get the child before serialising. */
2324 child1 = g_variant_get_child_value (variant, 0);
2325 data1 = g_variant_get_data_as_bytes (child1);
2326
2327 /* Serialise the parent variant. */
2328 g_variant_get_data (variant);
2329
2330 /* Get the child again after serialising — this uses a different code path. */
2331 child2 = g_variant_get_child_value (variant, 0);
2332 data2 = g_variant_get_data_as_bytes (child2);
2333
2334 /* Check things are equal. */
2335 g_assert_cmpvariant (child1, child2)do { GVariant *__v1 = (child1), *__v2 = (child2); if (!g_variant_equal
(__v1, __v2)) { gchar *__s1, *__s2, *__msg; __s1 = g_variant_print
(__v1, (!(0))); __s2 = g_variant_print (__v2, (!(0))); __msg
= g_strdup_printf ("assertion failed (" "child1" " == " "child2"
"): %s does not equal %s", __s1, __s2); g_assertion_message (
"GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2335, ((const char*) (__func__
)), __msg); g_free (__s1); g_free (__s2); g_free (__msg); } }
while (0);
2336 g_assert_true (g_bytes_equal (data1, data2))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_bytes_equal (data1, data2)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2336, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "g_bytes_equal (data1, data2)" "' should be TRUE"); }
while (0);
2337
2338 g_variant_unref (child2);
2339 g_variant_unref (child1);
2340 g_variant_unref (variant);
2341 g_bytes_unref (data2);
2342 g_bytes_unref (data1);
2343 g_variant_type_free (mv_type);
2344}
2345
2346static void
2347test_fuzz (gdouble *fuzziness)
2348{
2349 GVariantSerialised serialised;
2350 TreeInstance *tree;
2351
2352 /* make an instance */
2353 tree = tree_instance_new (NULL((void*)0), 3);
2354
2355 /* serialise it */
2356 serialise_tree (tree, &serialised);
2357
2358 g_assert_true (g_variant_serialised_is_normal (serialised))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_serialised_is_normal (serialised)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2358
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_serialised_is_normal (serialised)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2359 g_assert_true (check_tree (tree, serialised))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (check_tree (tree, serialised)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2359, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "check_tree (tree, serialised)" "' should be TRUE"); }
while (0);
2360
2361 if (serialised.size)
2362 {
2363 gboolean fuzzed = FALSE(0);
2364 gboolean a, b;
2365
2366 while (!fuzzed)
2367 {
2368 gsize i;
2369
2370 for (i = 0; i < serialised.size; i++)
2371 if (randomly (*fuzziness))
2372 {
2373 serialised.data[i] += g_test_rand_int_range (1, 256);
2374 fuzzed = TRUE(!(0));
2375 }
2376 }
2377
2378 /* at least one byte in the serialised data has changed.
2379 *
2380 * this means that at least one of the following is true:
2381 *
2382 * - the serialised data now represents a different value:
2383 * check_tree() will return FALSE
2384 *
2385 * - the serialised data is in non-normal form:
2386 * g_variant_serialiser_is_normal() will return FALSE
2387 *
2388 * we always do both checks to increase exposure of the serialiser
2389 * to corrupt data.
2390 */
2391 a = g_variant_serialised_is_normal (serialised);
2392 b = check_tree (tree, serialised);
2393
2394 g_assert_true (!a || !b)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (!a || !b) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0
; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2394, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "!a || !b" "' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2395 }
2396
2397 tree_instance_free (tree);
2398 g_free (serialised.data);
2399}

2402static void
2403test_fuzzes (gpointer data)
2404{
2405 gdouble fuzziness;
2406 int i;
2407
2408 fuzziness = GPOINTER_TO_INT (data)((gint) (glong) (data)) / 100.;
2409
2410 for (i = 0; i < 200; i++)
2411 test_fuzz (&fuzziness);
2412
2413 g_variant_type_info_assert_no_infos ();
2414}
2415
2416static GVariant *
2417tree_instance_get_gvariant (TreeInstance *tree)
2418{
2419 const GVariantType *type;
2420 GVariant *result;
2421
2422 type = (GVariantType *) g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (tree->info);
2423
2424 switch (g_variant_type_info_get_type_char (tree->info)(g_variant_type_info_get_type_string(tree->info)[0]))
2425 {
2426 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_MAYBE'm':
2427 {
2428 const GVariantType *child_type;
2429 GVariant *child;
2430
2431 if (tree->n_children)
2432 child = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[0]);
2433 else
2434 child = NULL((void*)0);
2435
2436 child_type = g_variant_type_element (type);
2437
2438 if (child != NULL((void*)0) && randomly (0.5))
2439 child_type = NULL((void*)0);
2440
2441 result = g_variant_new_maybe (child_type, child);
2442 }
2443 break;
2444
2445 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_ARRAY'a':
2446 {
2447 const GVariantType *child_type;
2448 GVariant **children;
2449 gsize i;
2450
2451 children = g_new (GVariant *, tree->n_children)(GVariant * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (tree->
n_children); gsize __s = sizeof (GVariant *); gpointer __p; if
(__s == 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
2452 for (i = 0; i < tree->n_children; i++)
2453 children[i] = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[i]);
2454
2455 child_type = g_variant_type_element (type);
2456
2457 if (i > 0 && randomly (0.5))
2458 child_type = NULL((void*)0);
2459
2460 result = g_variant_new_array (child_type, children, tree->n_children);
2461 g_free (children);
2462 }
2463 break;
2464
2465 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_TUPLE'(':
2466 {
2467 GVariant **children;
2468 gsize i;
2469
2470 children = g_new (GVariant *, tree->n_children)(GVariant * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (tree->
n_children); gsize __s = sizeof (GVariant *); gpointer __p; if
(__s == 1) __p = g_malloc (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p
(__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L
*2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
2471 for (i = 0; i < tree->n_children; i++)
2472 children[i] = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[i]);
2473
2474 result = g_variant_new_tuple (children, tree->n_children);
2475 g_free (children);
2476 }
2477 break;
2478
2479 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_DICT_ENTRY'{':
2480 {
2481 GVariant *key, *val;
2482
2483 g_assert_cmpuint (tree->n_children, ==, 2)do { guint64 __n1 = (tree->n_children), __n2 = (2); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2483, ((const char*) (__func__)), "tree->n_children" " "
"==" " " "2", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'
); } while (0);
2484
2485 key = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[0]);
2486 val = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[1]);
2487
2488 result = g_variant_new_dict_entry (key, val);
2489 }
2490 break;
2491
2492 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_VARIANT'v':
2493 {
2494 GVariant *value;
2495
2496 g_assert_cmpuint (tree->n_children, ==, 1)do { guint64 __n1 = (tree->n_children), __n2 = (1); if (__n1
== __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2496, ((const char*) (__func__)), "tree->n_children" " "
"==" " " "1", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'
); } while (0);
2497
2498 value = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree->children[0]);
2499 result = g_variant_new_variant (value);
2500 }
2501 break;
2502
2503 case 'b':
2504 result = g_variant_new_boolean (tree->data.integer > 0);
2505 break;
2506
2507 case 'y':
2508 result = g_variant_new_byte (tree->data.integer);
2509 break;
2510
2511 case 'n':
2512 result = g_variant_new_int16 (tree->data.integer);
2513 break;
2514
2515 case 'q':
2516 result = g_variant_new_uint16 (tree->data.integer);
2517 break;
2518
2519 case 'i':
2520 result = g_variant_new_int32 (tree->data.integer);
2521 break;
2522
2523 case 'u':
2524 result = g_variant_new_uint32 (tree->data.integer);
2525 break;
2526
2527 case 'x':
2528 result = g_variant_new_int64 (tree->data.integer);
2529 break;
2530
2531 case 't':
2532 result = g_variant_new_uint64 (tree->data.integer);
2533 break;
2534
2535 case 'h':
2536 result = g_variant_new_handle (tree->data.integer);
2537 break;
2538
2539 case 'd':
2540 result = g_variant_new_double (tree->data.floating);
2541 break;
2542
2543 case 's':
2544 result = g_variant_new_string (tree->data.string);
2545 break;
2546
2547 case 'o':
2548 result = g_variant_new_object_path (tree->data.string);
2549 break;
2550
2551 case 'g':
2552 result = g_variant_new_signature (tree->data.string);
2553 break;
2554
2555 default:
2556 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2556, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
2557 }
2558
2559 return result;
2560}
2561
2562static gboolean
2563tree_instance_check_gvariant (TreeInstance *tree,
2564 GVariant *value)
2565{
2566 const GVariantType *type;
2567
2568 type = (GVariantType *) g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (tree->info);
2569 g_assert_true (g_variant_is_of_type (value, type))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_is_of_type (value, type)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1
; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2569, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "g_variant_is_of_type (value, type)" "' should be TRUE"
); } while (0);
2570
2571 switch (g_variant_type_info_get_type_char (tree->info)(g_variant_type_info_get_type_string(tree->info)[0]))
2572 {
2573 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_MAYBE'm':
2574 {
2575 GVariant *child;
2576 gboolean equal;
2577
2578 child = g_variant_get_maybe (value);
2579
2580 if (child != NULL((void*)0) && tree->n_children == 1)
2581 equal = tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree->children[0], child);
2582 else if (child == NULL((void*)0) && tree->n_children == 0)
2583 equal = TRUE(!(0));
2584 else
2585 equal = FALSE(0);
2586
2587 if (child != NULL((void*)0))
2588 g_variant_unref (child);
2589
2590 return equal;
2591 }
2592 break;
2593
2594 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_ARRAY'a':
2595 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_TUPLE'(':
2596 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_DICT_ENTRY'{':
2597 {
2598 gsize i;
2599
2600 if (g_variant_n_children (value) != tree->n_children)
2601 return FALSE(0);
2602
2603 for (i = 0; i < tree->n_children; i++)
2604 {
2605 GVariant *child;
2606 gboolean equal;
2607
2608 child = g_variant_get_child_value (value, i);
2609 equal = tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree->children[i], child);
2610 g_variant_unref (child);
2611
2612 if (!equal)
2613 return FALSE(0);
2614 }
2615
2616 return TRUE(!(0));
2617 }
2618 break;
2619
2620 case G_VARIANT_TYPE_INFO_CHAR_VARIANT'v':
2621 {
2622 const gchar *str1, *str2;
2623 GVariant *child;
2624 gboolean equal;
2625
2626 child = g_variant_get_variant (value);
2627 str1 = g_variant_get_type_string (child);
2628 str2 = g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (tree->children[0]->info);
2629 /* GVariant only keeps one copy of type strings around */
2630 equal = str1 == str2 &&
2631 tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree->children[0], child);
2632
2633 g_variant_unref (child);
2634
2635 return equal;
2636 }
2637 break;
2638
2639 case 'b':
2640 return g_variant_get_boolean (value) == tree->data.integer;
2641
2642 case 'y':
2643 return g_variant_get_byte (value) == (guchar) tree->data.integer;
2644
2645 case 'n':
2646 return g_variant_get_int16 (value) == (gint16) tree->data.integer;
2647
2648 case 'q':
2649 return g_variant_get_uint16 (value) == (guint16) tree->data.integer;
2650
2651 case 'i':
2652 return g_variant_get_int32 (value) == (gint32) tree->data.integer;
2653
2654 case 'u':
2655 return g_variant_get_uint32 (value) == (guint32) tree->data.integer;
2656
2657 case 'x':
2658 return g_variant_get_int64 (value) == (gint64) tree->data.integer;
2659
2660 case 't':
2661 return g_variant_get_uint64 (value) == (guint64) tree->data.integer;
2662
2663 case 'h':
2664 return g_variant_get_handle (value) == (gint32) tree->data.integer;
2665
2666 case 'd':
2667 {
2668 gdouble floating = g_variant_get_double (value);
2669
2670 return memcmp (&floating, &tree->data.floating, sizeof floating) == 0;
2671 }
2672
2673 case 's':
2674 case 'o':
2675 case 'g':
2676 return strcmp (g_variant_get_string (value, NULL((void*)0)),
2677 tree->data.string) == 0;
2678
2679 default:
2680 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2680, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
2681 }
2682}
2683
2684static void
2685tree_instance_build_gvariant (TreeInstance *tree,
2686 GVariantBuilder *builder,
2687 gboolean guess_ok)
2688{
2689 const GVariantType *type;
2690
2691 type = (GVariantType *) g_variant_type_info_get_type_string (tree->info);
2692
2693 if (g_variant_type_is_container (type))
2694 {
2695 gsize i;
2696
2697 /* force GVariantBuilder to guess the type half the time */
2698 if (guess_ok && randomly (0.5))
2699 {
2700 if (g_variant_type_is_array (type) && tree->n_children)
2701 type = G_VARIANT_TYPE_ARRAY((const GVariantType *) "a*");
2702
2703 if (g_variant_type_is_maybe (type) && tree->n_children)
2704 type = G_VARIANT_TYPE_MAYBE((const GVariantType *) "m*");
2705
2706 if (g_variant_type_is_tuple (type))
2707 type = G_VARIANT_TYPE_TUPLE((const GVariantType *) "r");
2708
2709 if (g_variant_type_is_dict_entry (type))
2710 type = G_VARIANT_TYPE_DICT_ENTRY((const GVariantType *) "{?*}");
2711 }
2712 else
2713 guess_ok = FALSE(0);
2714
2715 g_variant_builder_open (builder, type);
2716
2717 for (i = 0; i < tree->n_children; i++)
2718 tree_instance_build_gvariant (tree->children[i], builder, guess_ok);
2719
2720 g_variant_builder_close (builder);
2721 }
2722 else
2723 g_variant_builder_add_value (builder, tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree));
2724}
2725
2726
2727static gboolean
2728tree_instance_check_iter (TreeInstance *tree,
2729 GVariantIter *iter)
2730{
2731 GVariant *value;
2732
2733 value = g_variant_iter_next_value (iter);
2734
2735 if (g_variant_is_container (value))
2736 {
2737 gsize i;
2738
2739 iter = g_variant_iter_new (value);
2740 g_variant_unref (value);
2741
2742 if (g_variant_iter_n_children (iter) != tree->n_children)
2743 {
2744 g_variant_iter_free (iter);
2745 return FALSE(0);
2746 }
2747
2748 for (i = 0; i < tree->n_children; i++)
2749 if (!tree_instance_check_iter (tree->children[i], iter))
2750 {
2751 g_variant_iter_free (iter);
2752 return FALSE(0);
2753 }
2754
2755 g_assert_null (g_variant_iter_next_value (iter))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((g_variant_iter_next_value (iter)) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2755
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_iter_next_value (iter)"
"' should be NULL"); } while (0);
2756 g_variant_iter_free (iter);
2757
2758 return TRUE(!(0));
2759 }
2760
2761 else
2762 {
2763 gboolean equal;
2764
2765 equal = tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value);
2766 g_variant_unref (value);
2767
2768 return equal;
2769 }

2772static void
2773test_container (void)
2774{
2775 TreeInstance *tree;
2776 GVariant *value;
2777 gchar *s1, *s2;
2778
2779 tree = tree_instance_new (NULL((void*)0), 3);
2780 value = g_variant_ref_sink (tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree));
2781
2782 s1 = g_variant_print (value, TRUE(!(0)));
2783 g_assert_true (tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2783
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2784
2785 g_variant_get_data (value);
2786
2787 s2 = g_variant_print (value, TRUE(!(0)));
2788 g_assert_true (tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2788
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "tree_instance_check_gvariant (tree, value)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2789
2790 g_assert_cmpstr (s1, ==, s2)do { const char *__s1 = (s1), *__s2 = (s2); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1
, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2790, ((const char*) (__func__)), "s1" " " "==" " " "s2", __s1
, "==", __s2); } while (0);
2791
2792 if (g_variant_is_container (value))
2793 {
2794 GVariantBuilder builder;
2795 GVariantIter iter;
2796 GVariant *built;
2797 GVariant *val;
2798 gchar *s3;
2799
2800 g_variant_builder_init (&builder, G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"));
2801 tree_instance_build_gvariant (tree, &builder, TRUE(!(0)));
2802 built = g_variant_builder_end (&builder);
2803 g_variant_ref_sink (built);
2804 g_variant_get_data (built);
2805 val = g_variant_get_variant (built);
2806
2807 s3 = g_variant_print (val, TRUE(!(0)));
2808 g_assert_cmpstr (s1, ==, s3)do { const char *__s1 = (s1), *__s2 = (s3); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1
, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2808, ((const char*) (__func__)), "s1" " " "==" " " "s3", __s1
, "==", __s2); } while (0);
2809
2810 g_variant_iter_init (&iter, built);
2811 g_assert_true (tree_instance_check_iter (tree, &iter))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (tree_instance_check_iter (tree, &iter)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2811
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "tree_instance_check_iter (tree, &iter)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2812 g_assert_null (g_variant_iter_next_value (&iter))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((g_variant_iter_next_value (&iter)) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2812
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_iter_next_value (&iter)"
"' should be NULL"); } while (0);
2813
2814 g_variant_unref (built);
2815 g_variant_unref (val);
2816 g_free (s3);
2817 }
2818
2819 tree_instance_free (tree);
2820 g_variant_unref (value);
2821 g_free (s2);
2822 g_free (s1);
2823}

2825static void
2826test_string (void)
2827{
2828 /* Test some different methods of creating strings */
2829 GVariant *v;
2830
2831 v = g_variant_new_string ("foo");
2832 g_assert_cmpstr (g_variant_get_string (v, NULL), ==, "foo")do { const char *__s1 = (g_variant_get_string (v, ((void*)0))
), *__s2 = ("foo"); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2832, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "g_variant_get_string (v, NULL)" " " "==" " " "\"foo\"", __s1
, "==", __s2); } while (0);
2833 g_variant_unref (v);
2834
2835
2836 v = g_variant_new_take_string (g_strdup ("foo"));
2837 g_assert_cmpstr (g_variant_get_string (v, NULL), ==, "foo")do { const char *__s1 = (g_variant_get_string (v, ((void*)0))
), *__s2 = ("foo"); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2837, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "g_variant_get_string (v, NULL)" " " "==" " " "\"foo\"", __s1
, "==", __s2); } while (0);
2838 g_variant_unref (v);
2839
2840 v = g_variant_new_printf ("%s %d", "foo", 123);
2841 g_assert_cmpstr (g_variant_get_string (v, NULL), ==, "foo 123")do { const char *__s1 = (g_variant_get_string (v, ((void*)0))
), *__s2 = ("foo 123"); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else
g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 2841, ((const char*) (__func__)), "g_variant_get_string (v, NULL)"
" " "==" " " "\"foo 123\"", __s1, "==", __s2); } while (0);
2842 g_variant_unref (v);
2843}
2844
2845static void
2846test_utf8 (void)
2847{
2848 const gchar invalid[] = "hello\xffworld";
2849 GVariant *value;
2850
2851 /* ensure that the test data is not valid utf8... */
2852 g_assert_false (g_utf8_validate (invalid, -1, NULL))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (!(g_utf8_validate (invalid, -1, ((void*)0)))) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2852
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_utf8_validate (invalid, -1, NULL)"
"' should be FALSE"); } while (0);
2853
2854 /* load the data untrusted */
2855 value = g_variant_new_from_data (G_VARIANT_TYPE_STRING((const GVariantType *) "s"),
2856 invalid, sizeof invalid,
2857 FALSE(0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
2858
2859 /* ensure that the problem is caught and we get valid UTF-8 */
2860 g_assert_true (g_utf8_validate (g_variant_get_string (value, NULL), -1, NULL))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_utf8_validate (g_variant_get_string (value, ((void*)0
)), -1, ((void*)0))) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2860, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "g_utf8_validate (g_variant_get_string (value, NULL), -1, NULL)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2861 g_variant_unref (value);
2862
2863
2864 /* now load it trusted */
2865 value = g_variant_new_from_data (G_VARIANT_TYPE_STRING((const GVariantType *) "s"),
2866 invalid, sizeof invalid,
2867 TRUE(!(0)), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
2868
2869 /* ensure we get the invalid data (ie: make sure that time wasn't
2870 * wasted on validating data that was marked as trusted)
2871 */
2872 g_assert_true (g_variant_get_string (value, NULL) == invalid)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_get_string (value, ((void*)0)) == invalid) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 2872
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_get_string (value, NULL) == invalid"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
2873 g_variant_unref (value);
2874}

3616 ...)
3617{

3619 gboolean hash;
3620 va_list ap;
3621
3622 hash = g_str_has_suffix (format, "#");
3623
3624 va_start (ap, format)__builtin_va_start(ap, format);
3625 g_variant_get_va (value, format, hash ? &endptr : NULL((void*)0), &ap);
3626 va_end (ap)__builtin_va_end(ap);
