3628 if (hash)
3629 g_assert_cmpint (*endptr, ==, '#')do { gint64 __n1 = (*endptr), __n2 = ('#'); if (__n1 == __n2)
; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 3629, ((const char*) (__func__)), "*endptr" " " "==" " " "'#'"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0);
3630}

3704
3705static void
3706test_hashing (void)
3707{
3708 GVariant *items[4096];
3709 GHashTable *table;
3710 gsize i;
3711
3712 table = g_hash_table_new_full (g_variant_hash, g_variant_equal,
3713 (GDestroyNotify ) g_variant_unref,
3714 NULL((void*)0));
3715
3716 for (i = 0; i < G_N_ELEMENTS (items)(sizeof (items) / sizeof ((items)[0])); i++)
3717 {
3718 TreeInstance *tree;
3719 gsize j;
3720
3721 again:
3722 tree = tree_instance_new (NULL((void*)0), 0);
3723 items[i] = tree_instance_get_gvariant (tree);
3724 tree_instance_free (tree);
3725
3726 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
3727 if (g_variant_equal (items[i], items[j]))
3728 {
3729 g_variant_unref (items[i]);
3730 goto again;
3731 }
3732
3733 g_hash_table_insert (table,
3734 g_variant_ref_sink (items[i]),
3735 GINT_TO_POINTER (i)((gpointer) (glong) (i)));
3736 }
3737
3738 for (i = 0; i < G_N_ELEMENTS (items)(sizeof (items) / sizeof ((items)[0])); i++)
3739 {
3740 gpointer result;
3741
3742 result = g_hash_table_lookup (table, items[i]);
3743 g_assert_cmpint (GPOINTER_TO_INT (result), ==, i)do { gint64 __n1 = (((gint) (glong) (result))), __n2 = (i); if
(__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 3743, ((const char*) (__func__)), "GPOINTER_TO_INT (result)"
" " "==" " " "i", (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2
, 'i'); } while (0);
3744 }
3745
3746 g_hash_table_unref (table);
3747
3748 g_variant_type_info_assert_no_infos ();
3749}

3751static void
3752test_gv_byteswap (void)
3753{
3754#if G_BYTE_ORDER1234 == G_LITTLE_ENDIAN1234
3755# define native16(x)x, 0 x, 0
3756# define swapped16(x)0, x 0, x
3757#else
3758# define native16(x)x, 0 0, x
3759# define swapped16(x)0, x x, 0
3760#endif
3761 /* all kinds of of crazy randomised testing already performed on the
3762 * byteswapper in the /gvariant/serialiser/byteswap test and all kinds
3763 * of crazy randomised testing performed against the serialiser
3764 * normalisation functions in the /gvariant/serialiser/fuzz/ tests.
3765 *
3766 * just test a few simple cases here to make sure they each work
3767 */
3768 guchar validbytes[] = { 'a', '\0', swapped16(66)0, 66, 2,
3769 0,
3770 'b', '\0', swapped16(77)0, 77, 2,
3771 5, 11 };
3772 guchar corruptbytes[] = { 'a', '\0', swapped16(66)0, 66, 2,
3773 0,
3774 'b', '\0', swapped16(77)0, 77, 2,
3775 6, 11 };
3776 guint valid_data[4], corrupt_data[4];
3777 GVariant *value, *swapped;
3778 gchar *string, *string2;
3779
3780 memcpy (valid_data, validbytes, sizeof validbytes);
3781 memcpy (corrupt_data, corruptbytes, sizeof corruptbytes);
3782
3783 /* trusted */
3784 value = g_variant_new_from_data (G_VARIANT_TYPE ("a(sn)")(g_variant_type_checked_ (("a(sn)"))),
3785 valid_data, sizeof validbytes, TRUE(!(0)),
3786 NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
3787 swapped = g_variant_byteswap (value);
3788 g_variant_unref (value);
3789 g_assert_cmpuint (g_variant_get_size (swapped), ==, 13)do { guint64 __n1 = (g_variant_get_size (swapped)), __n2 = (13
); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 3789, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "g_variant_get_size (swapped)" " " "==" " " "13", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
3790 string = g_variant_print (swapped, FALSE(0));
3791 g_variant_unref (swapped);
3792 g_assert_cmpstr (string, ==, "[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]")do { const char *__s1 = (string), *__s2 = ("[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]"
); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 3792, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "string" " " "==" " " "\"[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]\"", __s1,
"==", __s2); } while (0);
3793 g_free (string);
3794
3795 /* untrusted but valid */
3796 value = g_variant_new_from_data (G_VARIANT_TYPE ("a(sn)")(g_variant_type_checked_ (("a(sn)"))),
3797 valid_data, sizeof validbytes, FALSE(0),
3798 NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
3799 swapped = g_variant_byteswap (value);
3800 g_variant_unref (value);
3801 g_assert_cmpuint (g_variant_get_size (swapped), ==, 13)do { guint64 __n1 = (g_variant_get_size (swapped)), __n2 = (13
); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 3801, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "g_variant_get_size (swapped)" " " "==" " " "13", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
3802 string = g_variant_print (swapped, FALSE(0));
3803 g_variant_unref (swapped);
3804 g_assert_cmpstr (string, ==, "[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]")do { const char *__s1 = (string), *__s2 = ("[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]"
); if (g_strcmp0 (__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 3804, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "string" " " "==" " " "\"[('a', 66), ('b', 77)]\"", __s1,
"==", __s2); } while (0);
3805 g_free (string);
3806
3807 /* untrusted, invalid */
3808 value = g_variant_new_from_data (G_VARIANT_TYPE ("a(sn)")(g_variant_type_checked_ (("a(sn)"))),
3809 corrupt_data, sizeof corruptbytes, FALSE(0),
3810 NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
3811 string = g_variant_print (value, FALSE(0));
3812 swapped = g_variant_byteswap (value);
3813 g_variant_unref (value);
3814 g_assert_cmpuint (g_variant_get_size (swapped), ==, 13)do { guint64 __n1 = (g_variant_get_size (swapped)), __n2 = (13
); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 3814, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "g_variant_get_size (swapped)" " " "==" " " "13", (long double
) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while (0);
3815 value = g_variant_byteswap (swapped);
3816 g_variant_unref (swapped);
3817 string2 = g_variant_print (value, FALSE(0));
3818 g_assert_cmpuint (g_variant_get_size (value), ==, 13)do { guint64 __n1 = (g_variant_get_size (value)), __n2 = (13)
; if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"

), "g_variant_get_size (value)" " " "==" " " "13", (long double

3819 g_variant_unref (value);

(__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib"

, "==", __s2); } while (0);

3848 NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));

4109 };
4110 guint i;

4112 for (i = 0; i < G_N_ELEMENTS (test)(sizeof (test) / sizeof ((test)[0])); i += 3)

4115 GVariant *value;
4116

4118 * parameter of g_variant_parse() to set the length. This allows valgrind
4119 * to catch 1-byte heap buffer overflows. */

; if ((value) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"

), "'" "value" "' should be NULL"); } while (0);
4126

4130 g_error ("test %u: Can't find '%s' in '%s'", i / 3,
4131 test[i+2], error1->message);
4132
4133 if (!g_str_has_prefix (error1->message, test[i+1]))
4134 g_error ("test %u: Expected location '%s' in '%s'", i / 3,
4135 test[i+1], error1->message);
4136
4137 /* Test again with the nul terminator this time. The behaviour should be
4138 * the same. */
4139 value = g_variant_parse (NULL((void*)0), test[i], NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &error2);
4140 g_assert_null (value)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((value) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"

); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"

4151/* Test that parsing GVariant text format integers works at the boundaries of
4152 * those integer types. We’re especially interested in the handling of the most
4153 * negative numbers, since those can’t be represented in sign + absolute value
4154 * form. */
4155static void
4156test_parser_integer_bounds (void)
4157{
4158 GVariant *value = NULL((void*)0);
4159 GError *local_error = NULL((void*)0);
4160
4161#define test_bound(TYPE, type, text, expected_value) \
4162 value = g_variant_parse (G_VARIANT_TYPE_##TYPE, text, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &local_error); \
4163 g_assert_no_error (local_error)do { if (local_error) g_assertion_message_error ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 4163, ((const char*) (__func__)), "local_error", local_error
, 0, 0); } while (0); \
4164 g_assert_nonnull (value)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((value) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4164, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "value" "' should not be NULL"); } while (0); \
4165 g_assert_true (g_variant_is_of_type (value, G_VARIANT_TYPE_##TYPE))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_is_of_type (value, G_VARIANT_TYPE_##TYPE)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4165
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_is_of_type (value, G_VARIANT_TYPE_##TYPE)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0); \
4166 g_assert_cmpint (g_variant_get_##type (value), ==, expected_value)do { gint64 __n1 = (g_variant_get_##type (value)), __n2 = (expected_value
); if (__n1 == __n2) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpnum ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4166, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "g_variant_get_##type (value)" " " "==" " " "expected_value"
, (long double) __n1, "==", (long double) __n2, 'i'); } while
(0); \
4167 g_variant_unref (value)
4168
4169 test_bound (BYTE, byte, "0", 0);
4170 test_bound (BYTE, byte, "255", G_MAXUINT8((guint8) 0xff));
4171 test_bound (INT16, int16, "-32768", G_MININT16((gint16) (-((gint16) 0x7fff) - 1)));
4172 test_bound (INT16, int16, "32767", G_MAXINT16((gint16) 0x7fff));
4173 test_bound (INT32, int32, "-2147483648", G_MININT32((gint32) (-((gint32) 0x7fffffff) - 1)));
4174 test_bound (INT32, int32, "2147483647", G_MAXINT32((gint32) 0x7fffffff));
4175 test_bound (INT64, int64, "-9223372036854775808", G_MININT64((gint64) (-(0x7fffffffffffffffL) - (1L))));
4176 test_bound (INT64, int64, "9223372036854775807", G_MAXINT64(0x7fffffffffffffffL));
4177 test_bound (HANDLE, handle, "-2147483648", G_MININT32((gint32) (-((gint32) 0x7fffffff) - 1)));
4178 test_bound (HANDLE, handle, "2147483647", G_MAXINT32((gint32) 0x7fffffff));
4179
4180#undef test_bound
4181}

4183/* Test that #GVariants which recurse too deeply are rejected. */
4184static void
4185test_parser_recursion (void)
4186{
4187 GVariant *value = NULL((void*)0);
4188 GError *local_error = NULL((void*)0);
4189 const guint recursion_depth = G_VARIANT_MAX_RECURSION_DEPTH((gsize) 128) + 1;
4190 gchar *silly_dict = g_malloc0 (recursion_depth * 2 + 1);
4191 gsize i;
4192
4193 for (i = 0; i < recursion_depth; i++)
4194 {
4195 silly_dict[i] = '{';
4196 silly_dict[recursion_depth * 2 - i - 1] = '}';
4197 }
4198
4199 value = g_variant_parse (NULL((void*)0), silly_dict, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &local_error);
4200 g_assert_error (local_error, G_VARIANT_PARSE_ERROR, G_VARIANT_PARSE_ERROR_RECURSION)do { if (!local_error || (local_error)->domain != (g_variant_parse_error_quark
()) || (local_error)->code != G_VARIANT_PARSE_ERROR_RECURSION
) g_assertion_message_error ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 4200, ((const char*) (__func__)), "local_error", local_error
, (g_variant_parse_error_quark ()), G_VARIANT_PARSE_ERROR_RECURSION
); } while (0);
4201 g_assert_null (value)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((value) == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4201, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "value" "' should be NULL"); } while (0);
4202 g_error_free (local_error);
4203 g_free (silly_dict);
4204}

4351static void
4352test_lookup_value (void)
4353{
4354 struct {
4355 const gchar *dict, *key, *value;
4356 } cases[] = {
4357 { "@a{ss} {'x': 'y'}", "x", "'y'" },
4358 { "@a{ss} {'x': 'y'}", "y" },
4359 { "@a{os} {'/x': 'y'}", "/x", "'y'" },
4360 { "@a{os} {'/x': 'y'}", "/y" },
4361 { "@a{sv} {'x': <'y'>}", "x", "'y'" },
4362 { "@a{sv} {'x': <5>}", "x", "5" },
4363 { "@a{sv} {'x': <'y'>}", "y" }
4364 };
4365 gsize i;
4366
4367 for (i = 0; i < G_N_ELEMENTS (cases)(sizeof (cases) / sizeof ((cases)[0])); i++)
4368 {
4369 GVariant *dictionary;
4370 GVariant *value;
4371 gchar *p;
4372
4373 dictionary = g_variant_parse (NULL((void*)0), cases[i].dict, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
4374 value = g_variant_lookup_value (dictionary, cases[i].key, NULL((void*)0));
4375 g_variant_unref (dictionary);
4376
4377 if (value == NULL((void*)0) && cases[i].value == NULL((void*)0))
4378 continue;
4379
4380 g_assert_true (value && cases[i].value)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (value && cases[i].value) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4380, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "value && cases[i].value" "' should be TRUE")
; } while (0);
4381 p = g_variant_print (value, FALSE(0));
4382 g_assert_cmpstr (cases[i].value, ==, p)do { const char *__s1 = (cases[i].value), *__s2 = (p); if (g_strcmp0
(__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4382, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "cases[i].value" " " "==" " " "p", __s1, "==", __s2); } while
(0);

4422
4423static GVariant *
4424untrusted (GVariant *a)
4425{
4426 GVariant *b;
4427 const GVariantType *type;
4428 GBytes *bytes;
4429
4430 type = g_variant_get_type (a);
4431 bytes = g_variant_get_data_as_bytes (a);
4432 b = g_variant_new_from_bytes (type, bytes, FALSE(0));
4433 g_bytes_unref (bytes);
4434 g_variant_unref (a);
4435
4436 return b;
4437}

= g_strdup_printf ("assertion failed (" "a" " == " "b" "): %s does not equal %s"
, __s1, __s2); g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 4570, ((const char*) (__func__)), __msg); g_free (__s1); g_free
(__s2); g_free (__msg); } } while (0);
4571 g_variant_unref (a);
4572 g_variant_unref (b);
4573 a = untrusted (g_variant_new_boolean (FALSE(0)));
4574 b = g_variant_get_normal_form (a);
4575 g_assert_cmpvariant (a, b)do { GVariant *__v1 = (a), *__v2 = (b); if (!g_variant_equal (
__v1, __v2)) { gchar *__s1, *__s2, *__msg; __s1 = g_variant_print
(__v1, (!(0))); __s2 = g_variant_print (__v2, (!(0))); __msg
= g_strdup_printf ("assertion failed (" "a" " == " "b" "): %s does not equal %s"
, __s1, __s2); g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c"
, 4575, ((const char*) (__func__)), __msg); g_free (__s1); g_free
(__s2); g_free (__msg); } } while (0);
4576 g_variant_unref (a);

4665
4666static void
4667verify_gvariant_checksum (const gchar *sha256,
4668 GVariant *v)
4669
4670{
4671 gchar *checksum;
4672 checksum = g_compute_checksum_for_data (G_CHECKSUM_SHA256,
4673 g_variant_get_data (v),
4674 g_variant_get_size (v));
4675 g_assert_cmpstr (sha256, ==, checksum)do { const char *__s1 = (sha256), *__s2 = (checksum); if (g_strcmp0
(__s1, __s2) == 0) ; else g_assertion_message_cmpstr ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4675, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "sha256" " " "==" " " "checksum", __s1, "==", __s2); } while
(0);
4676 g_free (checksum);
4677}
4678
4679static void
4680verify_gvariant_checksum_va (const gchar *sha256,
4681 const gchar *fmt,
4682 ...)
4683{
4684 va_list args;
4685 GVariant *v;
4686
4687 va_start (args, fmt)__builtin_va_start(args, fmt);
4688
4689 v = g_variant_new_va (fmt, NULL((void*)0), &args);
4690 g_variant_ref_sink (v);
4691#if G_BYTE_ORDER1234 == G_BIG_ENDIAN4321
4692 {
4693 GVariant *byteswapped = g_variant_byteswap (v);
4694 g_variant_unref (v);
4695 v = byteswapped;
4696 }
4697#endif
4698
4699 va_end (args)__builtin_va_end(args);
4700
4701 verify_gvariant_checksum (sha256, v);
4702
4703 g_variant_unref (v);
4704}

4916/* Check that deeply nested variants are not considered in normal form when
4917 * deserialised from untrusted data.*/
4918static void
4919test_recursion_limits_variant_in_variant (void)
4920{
4921 GVariant *wrapper_variant = NULL((void*)0);
4922 gsize i;
4923 GBytes *bytes = NULL((void*)0);
4924 GVariant *deserialised_variant = NULL((void*)0);
4925
4926 /* Construct a hierarchy of variants, containing a single string. This is just
4927 * below the maximum recursion level, as a series of nested variant types. */
4928 wrapper_variant = g_variant_new_string ("hello");
4929
4930 for (i = 0; i < G_VARIANT_MAX_RECURSION_DEPTH((gsize) 128) - 1; i++)
4931 wrapper_variant = g_variant_new_variant (g_steal_pointer (&wrapper_variant)(0 ? (*(&wrapper_variant)) : (g_steal_pointer) (&wrapper_variant
)));
4932
4933 /* Serialise and deserialise it as untrusted data, to force normalisation. */
4934 bytes = g_variant_get_data_as_bytes (wrapper_variant);
4935 deserialised_variant = g_variant_new_from_bytes (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"),
4936 bytes, FALSE(0));
4937 g_assert_nonnull (deserialised_variant)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((deserialised_variant) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ =
1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else

, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "deserialised_variant" "' should not be NULL"
); } while (0);
4938 g_assert_true (g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant)) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4938
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);
4939
4940 g_bytes_unref (bytes);
4941 g_variant_unref (deserialised_variant);
4942
4943 /* Wrap it once more. Normalisation should now fail. */
4944 wrapper_variant = g_variant_new_variant (g_steal_pointer (&wrapper_variant)(0 ? (*(&wrapper_variant)) : (g_steal_pointer) (&wrapper_variant
)));
4945
4946 bytes = g_variant_get_data_as_bytes (wrapper_variant);
4947 deserialised_variant = g_variant_new_from_bytes (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"),
4948 bytes, FALSE(0));
4949 g_assert_nonnull (deserialised_variant)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((deserialised_variant) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ =
1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4949
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "deserialised_variant" "' should not be NULL"
); } while (0);
4950 g_assert_false (g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (!(g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant))) _g_boolean_var_
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else
g_assertion_message ("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 4950
, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant)"

4951

4953
4954 /* Deserialise it again, but trusted this time. This should succeed. */
4955 deserialised_variant = g_variant_new_from_bytes (G_VARIANT_TYPE_VARIANT((const GVariantType *) "v"),
4956 bytes, TRUE(!(0)));
4957 g_assert_nonnull (deserialised_variant)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((deserialised_variant) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ =

= 1; else _g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else

, ((const char*) (__func__)), "'" "g_variant_is_normal_form (deserialised_variant)"
"' should be TRUE"); } while (0);

5013 g_bytes_unref (bytes);

5090/* Test that constructing a #GVariant from data which is not correctly aligned
5091 * for the variant type is OK, by loading a variant from data at various offsets
5092 * which are aligned and unaligned. When unaligned, a slow construction path
5093 * should be taken. */
5094static void
5095test_unaligned_construction (void)
5096{
5097 const guint8 data[] = {
5098 0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06, 0x07,
5099 0x08, 0x09, 0x0A, 0x0B, 0x0C, 0x0D, 0x0E, 0x0F,
5100 };
5101 GVariant *variant = NULL((void*)0);
5102 GVariant *normal_variant = NULL((void*)0);
5103 gsize i, offset;
5104 const struct {
5105 const GVariantType *type;
5106 gsize size;
5107 gsize max_offset;
5108 } vectors[] = {
5109 { G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT64((const GVariantType *) "t"), sizeof (guint64), sizeof (guint64) },
5110 { G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT32((const GVariantType *) "u"), sizeof (guint32), sizeof (guint32) },
5111 { G_VARIANT_TYPE_UINT16((const GVariantType *) "q"), sizeof (guint16), sizeof (guint16) },
5112 { G_VARIANT_TYPE_BYTE((const GVariantType *) "y"), sizeof (guint8), 3 },
5113 };
5114
5115 G_STATIC_ASSERT (sizeof (guint64) * 2 <= sizeof (data))typedef char _GStaticAssertCompileTimeAssertion_42[(sizeof (guint64
) * 2 <= sizeof (data)) ? 1 : -1] __attribute__((__unused__
));
5116
5117 for (i = 0; i < G_N_ELEMENTS (vectors)(sizeof (vectors) / sizeof ((vectors)[0])); i++)
5118 {
5119 for (offset = 0; offset < vectors[i].max_offset; offset++)
5120 {
5121 variant = g_variant_new_from_data (vectors[i].type, data + offset,
5122 vectors[i].size,
5123 FALSE(0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
5124 g_assert_nonnull (variant)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((variant) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message ("GLib"
, "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 5124, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "'" "variant" "' should not be NULL"); } while (0);
5125
5126 normal_variant = g_variant_get_normal_form (variant);
5127 g_assert_nonnull (normal_variant)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if ((normal_variant) != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else
_g_boolean_var_ = 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message
("GLib", "../glib/tests/gvariant.c", 5127, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "'" "normal_variant" "' should not be NULL"); } while (0);
5128
5129 g_variant_unref (normal_variant);
5130 g_variant_unref (variant);
5131 }
5132 }
5133}
